article.headline: S. Dakota St. 80, IUPUI 65
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Brayden Carlson scored 18 points and the other four starters scored in double figures for South Dakota State in an 80-68 victory over IUPUI on Saturday. South Dakota State (15-6, 6-2 Summit) also got 12 points from Nate Wolters, 11 from Jordan Dykstra and 10 each from Tony Fiegen and Chad White. Carlson connected on three 3-point shots and grabbed seven rebounds. Wolters had seven assists. The South Dakota State bench also was productive, outscoring the IUPUI reserves 19-3. Mitchell Patton and Greg Rice each scored 17 points to lead IUPUI (6-16, 1-7). Donovan Gibbs scored 14 points and P.J. Hubert added 12. Patton had 11 rebounds and Gibbs had 10 rebounds.
